(32, 23, 'ENG', 'Formation Of New Districts ', '<div>Chhattisgarh will have 9 new districts with effect from January 2012, taking the total number of districts in the state to 27. These districts will be Sukma, Kondagaon, Gariabandh, Balodabazar, Balod, Bemetera, Mungeli, Surajpur and Balrampur.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>This was announced by the Chhattisgarh Chief Minister Raman Singh on 15 August 2011 while addressing the people on the occasion of the Independence Day at the police parade ground in Raipur. This step will be a mile stone in the administrative history of the state.</div>', '1450163717-cminitiativeb.jpg', 'Chattisgarh Districts', '1450163717-cminitiativem.jpg', 'Image', 1, '2015-12-15 07:15:17', '2011-08-15'),
(33, 23, 'ENG', 'Chhattisgarh Enforces Citizens\' Charter', 'In an important decision, the BJP government in Chhattisgarh today said it has enforced Citizens\' Charter in the state while bringing in 139 public services under it.', '1450163921-cminitiativeb.jpg', 'Citizen Character', '1450163921-cminitiativem.jpg', 'Image', 1, '2015-12-15 07:18:41', '2012-01-03'),
(34, 23, 'ENG', 'Krishak Jeevan Jyoti Scheme', 'In yet another significant move to strengthen the agriculture sector of the State, the State Cabinet on Tuesday approved the amended Krishak Jeevan Jyoti Yojana under which one member each of farmers\' family will be eligible to consume 6000 units of electricity on the use of electric motor pump up to 3 horse power and 7500 units of electricity will be free of cost for farmers using electric motor pump of capacity between 3 and 5 horse power for irrigation purpose in one fiscal. The farmer-friendly decision will result in an additional burden of Rs 255 crore per annum on the State Government. Farmers with 5 HP irrigation pumps are being provided with 6000 units of power without any charges, on an annual basis. Availability of adequate fertilizers and seeds has been ensured. From January 2008, Chhattisgarh become the country’s first state to enjoy load shedding-free power supply.', '1450164212-cminitiativeb.jpg', 'Jeevan Jyoti Scheme', '1450164212-cminitiativem.jpg', 'Image', 1, '2016-01-13 06:29:32', '2012-06-20'),
(35, 23, 'ENG', 'Atal Vihar Yojana', 'Chhattisgarh government will construct about 100,000 houses for poor and middle class people across the state under a scheme named after former Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee.The Atal Vihar Yojana would be launched in 40 towns in the state and would be completed in three years. The work on the ambitious housing project that had been designed with an estimated cost of Rs 11,800 crore would start later this month.', '1450165253-cminitiativeb.jpg', 'Atal Vihar Yojana', '1450165253-cminitiativem.jpg', 'Image', 1, '2016-01-13 06:28:59', '2011-07-07'),
(38, 0, 'ENG', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, '0', '0', 0, '2016-03-11 13:47:40', '0000-00-00'),
(44, 26, 'ENG', 'My Vision', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"background: white;\">Our Government took over the reins of power at a time when </span>the socio-economic condition of the State was at an all-time low. There was a complete breakdown of law and order and extremism was at its peak.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">We worked relentlessly for the upliftment of the society by focusing on industry, infrastructure, production, education, health, women, children, minorities and how to eradicate extremism, prejudices, and poverty from the State.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">In 2001, the power sector bore losses in distribution making it difficult for the Assam Electricity Board to cover its costs and supply adequate electricity. We promoted the idea of installation of digital meters in every household to overcome the loss and to benefit people in the long run.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Similarly, infrastructure development was the next key area that we looked into to bridge the gap between rural and urban areas.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">The achievements of Assam are well documented and people have witnessed by themselves.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">In a quest to attain peace, prosperity and growth, we envisage Assam would be an example for the other states in India by 2030.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">We will ensure a society that is free from hunger and malnutrition.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">For sustainable development; agricultural growth, proper healthcare facilities, quality education, women empowerment and employment would continue to be on our priority list.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Looking at the trend of recovery in agriculture, we intend to accelerate more growth by finding the loopholes and filling those loopholes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Assam Vision 2030 aims at reducing the child and maternal mortality rate to a minimum but it will also strive to bring down the rising epidemics in the state such as HIV, Cancer to a grinding halt resulting in an increase in &nbsp;life expectancy.&nbsp;</p>', '1458545271-cminitiativeb.jpg', 'My Vision', '1458545271-cminitiativem.jpg', 'Image', 1, '2018-03-24 15:24:01', '2016-03-01'),
