(9, 17, 18, 'ENG', '9423684600', 'http://rajyavardhanrathore.in/', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;\">Rajyavardhan Singh Rathore was born in Jaisalmer (Rajasthan) on January 29, 1970, as his maternal grandfather was posted there. He is a Rathore (bika) descendant of the first king of Bikaner Rao Bikaji. He belongs to a Rajput family based in Bikaner.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;\">Colonel Rajyavardhan Singh Rathore is an Veteran Indian shooter and politician (union minister), who rose to fame after winning the Silver Medal in Men\'s Double Trap at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens. He is the first sportsperson to win individual Silver for India since Norman Pritchard, who won two Silver Medals at the 1900 Paris Olympics. Rathore hails from Jaisalmer, Rajasthan.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;\">Rathore graduated from the National Defence Academy, and since served in the Indian Army where he retired as a Colonel in 2013, before joining politics. He is a member of the Bharatiya Janata Party. He won his first Lok Sabha election in 2014 and is currently the Minister of State for Ministry of Information and Broadcasting under the Narendra Modi government.</p>\r\n	', 'Array', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;\">On 10 September 2013, Rathore joined Bharatiya Janata Party after\r\ntaking voluntary retirement from the Indian Army. He was elected as a MP in the\r\n2014 Lok Sabha election from Jaipur Rural constituency. On 9 November 2014, he\r\nwas sworn-in as the Minister of State for Information &amp; Broadcasting, under\r\nthe Narendra Modi government. </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p><u>Achievements</u></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;\"><u><br></u></p><ul style=\"margin-top:0in\" type=\"disc\">\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\">1989- Blazer\r\n     (Highest sports award at the National Defence Academy, Pune, India).<o:p></o:p></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\">1990 -\r\n     Sword of Honour (For the Best All Round Officer Cadet at the Indian\r\n     Military Academy).<o:p></o:p></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\">1990 -\r\n     Sikh Regiment Gold Medal (For the Best Sportsmen at the Indian Military\r\n     Academy).<o:p></o:p></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\">2004-2005\r\n     - the Rajiv Gandhi Khel Ratna (Highest Sporting Honour of India).<o:p></o:p></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\">2003-2004\r\n     - Arjuna Award<o:p></o:p></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\">Rathore\r\n     is a recipient of the Padma Shri, a civilian award from the Government of\r\n     India<o:p></o:p></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\">Ati\r\n     Vishisht Seva Medal (AVSM), military award for exceptional service, presented\r\n     by the President of India on behalf of the Government of India.<o:p></o:p></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\">Rathore\r\n     was the chosen flag bearer for India during the 2008 Summer Olympics in\r\n     Beijing, China.<o:p></o:p></li>\r\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\">Rathore\r\n     was the chosen flag bearer for India during the 2006 Commonwealth Games in\r\n     Melbourne, Australia.</li></ul>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -0.25in;\"><br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -0.25in;\"><br></p>', 'Array', '<div>Colonel Rajyavardhan Singh Rathore is an Veteran Indian shooter and politician (union minister), who rose to fame after winning the Silver Medal in Men\'s Double Trap at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens.[1] He is the first sportsperson to win an individual Silver for India since Norman Pritchard, who won two Silver Medals at the 1900 Paris Olympics.[2] Rathore hails from Jaisalmer, Rajasthan.</div><div><br></div><div>Rathore graduated from the National Defence Academy, and since served in the Indian Army where he retired as a Colonel in 2013, before joining politics. He is a member of the Bharatiya Janata Party.[3] He won his first Lok Sabha election in 2014 and is currently the Minister of State for Ministry of Information and Broadcasting under the Narendra Modi government.</div>', '1451971358-socdimg.jpg', '1443015542-pp.jpg', '1442234701-wp.jpg', 'chillyrathore', '<a class=\"twitter-timeline\" href=\"https://twitter.com/Ra_THORe\" data-widget-id=\"646617054674485248\" width=\"310\"  height=\"450\">Tweets by @Ra_THORe</a>\r\n<script>!function(d,s,id){var js,fjs=d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0],p=/^http:/.test(d.location)?\'http\':\'https\';if(!d.getElementById(id)){js=d.createElement(s);js.id=id;js.src=p+\"://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\";fjs.parentNode.insertBefore(js,fjs);}}(document,\"script\",\"twitter-wjs\");</script>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '#07782f', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(10, 22, 23, 'ENG', '0771 2331000', 'http://www.drramansingh.in/', NULL, '<div>Raman Singh (born 15 October 1952) is an Indian politician and is the Chief Minister of Chhattisgarh state since 7 December 2003. He is a member of the Bharatiya Janata Party.</div><div><br></div><div>Raman Singh was born on 15 October 1952 in a Rajput family. His father being Vighnaharan Singh Thakur and his mother, Sudha Singh. He is a doctor of Ayurvedic Medicine and is married to Veena Singh. His son Abhishek is a qualified mechanical engineer and currently serving as Member of Parliament from Rajnandgaon constituency and his daughter Asmita is a practising dental surgeon.</div><div><br></div><div>Raman Singh is a member of the Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh.</div>', '1450162789-pdimg.jpg', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Dr. Raman Singh joined the Bharatiya Jan Sangh as a youth member and was the president of youth wing in Kawardha in 1976-77.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">He progressed to become a councilor of Kawardha municipality in 1983.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">He was elected to Madhya Pradesh Legislative Assembly consecutively in 1990 and 1993.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">In 1999 he was elected to the 13th Lok Sabha from the Rajnandgaon constituency in Chhattisgarh. In the government of Atal Bihari Vajpayee, Singh became the Union Minister of State for Commerce and Industry from 1999 to 2003. He was later named as President of the Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP) in the new state of Chhattisgarh, and led the party to a victory in the 2003 state Assembly elections. With the other main contender for the Chief Minister\'s post, Dilip Singh Judeo, caught in the midst of a scam, the BJP leadership named Raman Singh as Chhattisgarh\'s second Chief Minister, and the first person to be elected to that post.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">He has received praise for his organizational abilities, as reflected in his state\'s position with regard to implementation of a programme to improve the conditions of Scheduled Tribes and Scheduled Castes. The United Nations has also recognised the work done in Chhattisgarh under his leadership and the fiscal management of the state is another aspect for which he is known.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">He banned naxalite organisations in Chhattisgarh in 2005 under the \"Salwa Judum\" initiative, a move supported by the opposition party as well, led by Mahendra Karma who was assassinated by naxalites on 25 May 2013. Singh was sworn in for his second term on December 12, 2008. On 8th Dec 2013 he has been re elected as the chief minister of the state.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">He successfully won election 2013 for his 3rd tenure as a CM of Chhattisgarh.</p>', '1450162789-poldimg.jpg', '<div>Raman Singh (born 15 October 1952) is an Indian politician and is the Chief Minister of Chhattisgarh state since 7 December 2003. He is a member of the Bharatiya Janata Party.</div><div><br></div><div>Raman Singh was born on 15 October 1952 in a Rajput family. His father being Vighnaharan Singh Thakur and his mother, Sudha Singh. He is a doctor of Ayurvedic Medicine and is married to Veena Singh. His son Abhishek is a qualified mechanical engineer and currently serving as Member of Parliament from Rajnandgaon constituency and his daughter Asmita is a practising dental surgeon.</div><div><br></div><div>Raman Singh is a member of the Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh.</div>', '1450162789-socdimg.jpg', '1450162789-pp.jpg', '1450162789-wp.jpg', 'drramansingh.official', '<a class=\"twitter-timeline\" href=\"https://twitter.com/drramansingh\" data-widget-id=\"687162390887071744\" width=\"310\"  height=\"450\">Tweets by @drramansingh</a>\r\n<script>!function(d,s,id){var js,fjs=d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0],p=/^http:/.test(d.location)?\'http\':\'https\';if(!d.getElementById(id)){js=d.createElement(s);js.id=id;js.src=p+\"://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\";fjs.parentNode.insertBefore(js,fjs);}}(document,\"script\",\"twitter-wjs\");</script>', NULL, NULL, 'Chief Minister of Chattisgarh', '#06792f', '1450162789-hbg.jpg', NULL, NULL),
(11, 0, 26, 'ENG', '2266188', 'http://tarungogoi.in/index.php', NULL, '<div>Shri Tarun Gogoi was born on October 11, 1934 at Rangajan Tea Estate in Jorhat district. He was a student of J.B. College, Jorhat wherefrom he took his B.A. Degree. He studied Law and took LLB Degree from Guwahati University. Shri. Gogoi started his career as a lawyer and simultaneously engaged himself in socio-political activities. Since student-life, qualities of leadership were evident in him when he held important positions in Students\' Unions including Commandership of Students\' Volunteer Corps.</div><div><br></div><div>Shri. Gogoi is a widely-traveled man. His favorite pastime is reading and gardening. He loves sports too. He married Smt. Dolly Gogoi in 1972 and they are blessed with a son and a daughter.</div><div><br></div><div>Shri. Gogoi is elected as Member of Assam Legislative Assembly on 13th May&nbsp;2011 and assumed the office of the Chief Minister, Assam on 18th May&nbsp;2011.</div><div><br></div><div>Shri. Gogoi, during his colorful career, also adored important positions as Director of Vayudoot, Member of Bar Council of Assam and Chairman, Assam small Industries Development Corporation.</div>', '1454051333-pdimg.jpg', '<div>• In 1968, Shri. Gogoi was elected as a member of Jorhat Municipal Board. By this time, he established his guts as a capable youth leader of Assam. Late Prime Minister Indira Gandhi spotted this promising young talent and in 1971 entrusted him with the responsibility of organizing the youth community of the State. In that year itself i.e. 1971, Shri. Gogoi was elected to the 5th Lok Sabha. In 1976, he became the Joint Secretary of All India Congress Committee. He was re-elected to the 6th Lok Sabha in 1977. Then again, he was re-elected to the 7th Lok Sabha in 1983 and he became the Joint Secretary of AICC up to 1985. He became the General Secretary of All India Congress Committee in 1985. During 1986-90, he served as the President of Assam Pradesh Congress (I) Committee.</div><div><br></div><div>• For the 4th time, he was elected to the 10th Lok Sabha in 1991.</div><div><br></div><div>• During 1991-93, he was the Union Minister of Food (Independent Charge). From 1993 to 1995, he held the portfolio of Food Processing Industry as the Union Minister of State (Independent Charge).</div><div><br></div><div>• During 1997-98, he was elected Member of Assam Legislative Assembly from Margherita Constituency. He was elected as a Member of Parliament for the fifth time in 1998 to the 12th Lok Sabha. Again in 1999, Shri. Gogoi was re-elected to the 13th Lok Sabha. This is his sixth tenure as a Member of Parliament. Since 1996, he has been the President of the Assam Pradesh Congress Committee.</div><div><br></div><div>• Shri. Tarun Gogoi assumed the office of Chief Minister, Assam on 18th May 2001. In the month of September 2001 he has also been elected as Member of Assam Legislative Assembly.</div><div><br></div><div>• Shri. Gogoi was elected as Member of Assam Legislative Assembly on 11th May 2006 and he assumed the office of Chief Minister, Assam on 14th May 2006.</div><div><br></div><div>• Shri. Gogoi is elected as Member of Assam Legislative Assembly on 13th May 2011 and he assumed the Office of the Chief Minister, Assam on 18th May 2011.</div>', '1454051544-poldimg.jpg', '<div>Shri Gogoi had traveled many countries. His favorite pastime is reading and gardening. He also has a flair for sports like Golf, Cricket, Football and Tennis.</div><div><br></div><div>Shri. Gogoi held the following positions:&nbsp;</div><div>• Director, Vayudoot</div><div>• Chairman, Assam Small Scale Industries Development Corporation</div><div>• Vice-President J.B. College Students\' Union</div><div>• Vice-President, Inter College Students\' Union</div><div>• Joint Secretary, Jorhat Law College</div><div>• Commander, Students\' Volunteer Corps</div><div><br></div><div>Social and cultural activities:</div><div>• Treasurer, All Assam Moina Parijat &amp; Children\'s Organizations&nbsp;</div><div>• Chairman, Bharat Yuvak Samaj.</div>', '1454051333-socdimg.jpg', '0', '0', 'OfficialTarunGogoi', '<a class=\"twitter-timeline\" href=\"https://twitter.com/tarun_gogoi\" data-widget-id=\"692711972043796480\"  width=\"310\"  height=\"450\">Tweets by @tarun_gogoi</a>\r\n<script>!function(d,s,id){var js,fjs=d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0],p=/^http:/.test(d.location)?\'http\':\'https\';if(!d.getElementById(id)){js=d.createElement(s);js.id=id;js.src=p+\"://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\";fjs.parentNode.insertBefore(js,fjs);}}(document,\"script\",\"twitter-wjs\");</script>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '#06792f', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(12, 0, 29, 'ENG', '9890811111', 'http://jagdishmulik.com/', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Mangal&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Jagdish Mulik is\r\nan MLA of Wadgaon Sheri, Pune from BJP. People from Pune are already\r\nfamiliar with this family. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: Mangal, serif;\">The Mulik family\r\nwas known in Vadgaon for doing their business with honesty and integrity. While\r\ndoing business, you also owe to your community and nation and you should try\r\nyour best to do some community service and social commitment according to the\r\nrites. Jagdish Mulik began his work from BJP on a variety of topics.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: Mangal, serif;\">He attributed\r\nthis work with zeal and determination in Pune Municipal Corporation. He also\r\nworked on tree conservation committee and left an ever lasting impression. He\r\nbegan his career as small activist from the beginning and today lead the\r\npeople of the as city party secretary.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: Mangal, serif; font-size: 11pt;\">In the 2014 assembly elections, people from Vadagaon Sheri assembly (constituency) elected him by majority and gave him the\r\nopportunity to work as a youngest legislator from Western Maharashtra.</span></p>', '1459337591-pdimg.jpg', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">2011: General Secretary of BJP Yuva Morcha student Agadi,\r\nPune City </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">2005: State Executive Member of Maharashtra BJP Yuva Morcha </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">2005: Member of BJP Yuva Morcha Tree Conservation Committee</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">2005: State Vice President of Maharashtra BJP Yuva Morcha </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">2011: Secretary of Pune city BJP </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">2013: General Secretary of Pune city BJP</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">2014: MLA, Vadgaonsheri Assembly</p>', '1459337591-poldimg.jpg', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Jagdish Mulik is working honestly and selflessly for the people of Vadgaon Sheri Constituency. He is completely involved in &nbsp;resolving problems of citizen\'s need such a road, water, and try to be honest in\r\nall aspects. He is also trying hard for improving electricity, transport, health, cleaning issues and doing various\r\ndevelopment works. He also funds the government\'s groups and other groups doing social activities.</p>', '1459337591-socdimg.jpg', '0', '0', 'jagdish.mulik.7', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '#06792f', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(13, 29, 30, 'ENG', '9422769444', 'http://voterfirst.com/', NULL, NULL, '1462371012-pdimg.gif', NULL, '1459496044-poldimg.jpeg', NULL, '1459495963-socdimg.jpg', '1459495963-pp.jpg', '0', 'narhari.zirwal', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '#06792f', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(14, 30, 31, 'ENG', '9422507011', 'http://voterfirst.com', NULL, '<div>Name: R. N. Patel</div><div>Staff Number.: 08074</div><div>Date of Birth: 28/12/1959</div><div>Qualifications: B.E. (Electronics)</div><div>Date of Entry in the Department: 17.09.1984</div><div>Entered in Department as: ADET</div><div>Field of Specialization: Transmission</div><div>Present Grade &amp; Continuous Appointment: SAG, w.e.f 13.6.2003</div><div>Present Post: Sr. General Manager, Nagpur Telephone District w.e.f 10/06/2013</div>', '0', '<div>Shri R.N. Patel joined the Nagpur Telecom District in June 2013 and is working in the capacity of Head of Telecom. District, Nagpur.</div><div><br></div><div>Shri Patel had a brilliant academic career. He did B.E. in Electronics in 1982 from Maulana Azad College of Technology (presently re-christened as Maulana Azad National Institute of Technology) Bhopal. He belongs to the 1982- Batch of the I.T.S. cadre which he qualified through Union Public Service Commission. During the period from 1982 to joining the Dept. of Telecom. He served in U.P. Electronics for 4 months and with the Oil and Natural Gas Commission, Ahmedabad for about one year and eight months.</div><div><br></div><div>While serving as Telecom Engineer-cum-Manager, he worked in various fields and units of Telecommunications, which includes Projects, Operation and Maintenance of Switching and Transmission, Wireless Mobile services, i.e., GSM and CDMA Technology and also has the distinction of serving in the capacity of General Manager Telecom. Dist. at Indore (Madhya Pradesh), Nadiad (Gujarat) and is presently at the helm of affairs Telecom. Services at Nagpur as Sr. General Manager, Telecom. District, Bharat Sanchar Nigam Ltd.</div><div><br></div><div>He has specialized in Long Distance Transmission and Telecom. Traffic Management. On behalf of the Government of India, he had the opportunity to travel abroad on deputation on overseas training for specialization in International Traffic Management at Tokyo, Japan. He had delivered lectures at Symbiosis Pune on Spectrum Management and Telecom. Management.</div>', '0', '<div>Shri is a die-hard workaholic, deeply dedicated to his career, he also has keen interest in sports and music. In his college days he participated in Hockey and Volleyball tournaments. Presently he plays Lawn Tennis and has the credit of representing Madhya Pradesh Telecom Circle in All India B.S.N.L. Sports Tournament five times.</div><div><br></div><div>He has been conferred the Life Membership of Indian Institute of Public Administration, New Delhi and is a Fellow Member of Institute of Engineers and Telecommunication Engineers, &nbsp;New Delhi.</div>', '0', '0', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '#000000', NULL, NULL, NULL),
(15, 31, 32, 'ENG', '07312570067', 'http://bhaiyyumaharaj.com/', 'Every element of this world is temporary. If anything is timless, they are the thoughts and views. When considerations are based on spirituality, they remain for ages!', '<div>Param Pujya Rastra Sant, Shri Udaysingh Deshmukh, better known as Bhaiyyu Maharaj, is a Saint by all the dictionary definitions, The handsome, well built, charismatic, learned, talented and gifted Guru is in his early thirties and has been well recognized as the Rastra Saint (“राष्ट्र संत”), from his age of five The Saint is always compassionate towards the woes and worries of the people. The woes and worries could be physical, spiritual or otherwise; but a Saint is concerned about providing solace to the difficulties faced by the common man. Param Pujya Bhaiyyu Maharaj performs each and every of these but does some things neigh many more than these.</div><div><br></div><div>Uday Singh Deshmukh (born 29 April 1968) usually known as Bhaiyyu Maharaj &amp; Gurudev, is a spiritual guru &amp; founder of Shri Sadguru Datta Dharmik Evam Paramarthik Trust Indore which aims at serving humanity in various ways. He is well known among Political circles of Maharashtra, Madhya Pradesh &amp; Gujrat. Under his guidance the trust does a huge amount of work to uplift the backward, downtrodden &amp; poor sections in states of Maharashtra, Madhya Pradesh &amp; Gujarat.</div><div><br></div><div>At the age of 37, he is considered one of the youngest spiritual teachers in the world. We are the blessed and the most fortunate ones to be under the spiritual guidance of Guru Bhaiyyu Maharaj.Bhaiyyu Maharaj has set up Ashrams in various cities in Maharashtra and Madhya Pradesh. The main Ashram situated in Indore, SHRI SADGURU DATTA DHARMIK EVAM PARMARTHIK TRUST, located at BH-16, Pandit Dindayal Upadhyay Nagar (Bharat Mata Mandir) Sukhlia, Indore. The Ashram is a center where numerous spiritual and social projects and discussions are continuously held. Hundreds of devotees visit the Ashram to pay their respects and receive his blessings. It is strongly believed (and experienced) by his devotees that Bhaiyyu Maharaj looks to the welfare of his devotees. There are many instances reported by his devotees and disciples of his appearing in their midst during crises.</div><div><br></div><div>Bhaiyyu Maharaj has his headquarters in Indore, though he does not stay here always. He mainly tours Maharashtra for development of projects where he has numerous disciples and devotees who organize discourses on spiritual and practical ways of life.</div><div><br></div><div>Awards Won:</div><div>(1) Doctor of Literature from the D. Y. Patil University, (Kolhapur) 2016</div><div>(2) Ahinsha Ratan Award, 2013</div><div>(3)Rajiv Gandhi Excellence Award, 2014&nbsp;</div><div>(4)Vidharbh Bhooshan Award, 2016</div><div>(5) Indore Ratan Award, 2015</div>', '0', '<div>Principles bring concentration in life. Principles get Ganga in our life by way of concentration and aim. The Ganga brings fulfillment by continuous pleasure and generate self-satisfaction in life. Everybody wants that his life to be peaceful and contended. One decides principles with reference to need of epoch, that it be aim of attainment of supreme lord or aim of service of society. Everyone does have principles in life. The one whose principles are based on human values and think about social welfare are called as seers on this earth. Param Pujya Gurudev always thinks about welfare of society.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Gurudev though looks simple in behavior, but observes the following principles profoundly.&nbsp;</div><div>•&nbsp;For achieving good aim positive thinking is essential.&nbsp;</div><div>•&nbsp;To bring subtleness in practice it is essential to have source of temperament i.e. Bhav Tatva.&nbsp;</div><div>•&nbsp;One shall not permit devaluation of character.&nbsp;</div><div>•&nbsp;One shall not use abusive language to anybody.</div><div>•&nbsp;By way of Sankaras we can get rid of bad values and bad deeds from our consciousness.&nbsp;</div><div>•&nbsp;Youth is the most precious wealth of nation.</div><div>•&nbsp;The development of character of persons should go beyond religion, caste, sects or political associations.</div><div>•&nbsp;Personality development of child gets triggered first from home&nbsp;</div><div>•&nbsp;In personal life, instead of running after glittering materialism one should balance the situation.</div><div>•&nbsp;Try to build character. Don’t waste life for just lust, desires and greed.&nbsp;</div><div>•&nbsp;Understand the purpose of your life and make it meaningful for others too.</div>', '0', '<div>Dharma of sun is to impart energy to universe as soon it rises. Magnanimity of its light is bestowed upon both living and unanimated equally. Suns rays swallow darkness of life.</div><div><br></div><div>Sun is inspiration and symbol for the detached actions (Nishkam Karma). Sun never bothers about who is benefited by its rays of light. Sun is goddess exemplifying sacrifice, dedication, magnificence, service and detached action. Inspired by suns goodness, in this short life span let us do some good work for meaningful existence in society. Similarly duty of mankind is a chain of personnel relationship, strong base, warmth, love and self respect which joins them together as well as fulfills nation, society and humanism.</div><div><br></div><div>Today there are many problems and misfortunes in society. Which are like gloom of darkness surrounds all of us. We need energy of virtues (Sadgunas) to come out of such glooms. We need to adopt work approach based on virtues by which not only we can develop ourselves but also society and nation. Today above thoughts can be imbibed and strengthen by elderly persons shouldering their responsibility and younger ones as their duty. Wherever caste based political leadership is at the center stage, development cannot follow right kind of trajectory. Our small quantum of effort in right direction can be immensely helpful in development of society. We need to enhance the horizons of our thinking. We are born on this land, family and society has supported us, also ignited lamp of values so as to create true personality. If so then we need to think about our society and guide our efforts for its development. Egoless person can only work for society, nation and humanity. One can understand others only if himself devoid of ego.</div><div><br></div><div>Let us together create India, where every household is full of bliss and enlightened by the light of values welcoming sunrise (Suryodaya). This is our Suryodaya Dharma.</div>', '0', '0', '0', 'bhaiyyumaharaj', '<a class=\"twitter-timeline\"  href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=bhaiyujimaharaj\" data-widget-id=\"743062506583658498\">Tweets about bhaiyujimaharaj</a>\r\n            <script>!function(d,s,id){var js,fjs=d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0],p=/^http:/.test(d.location)?\'http\':\'https\';if(!d.getElementById(id)){js=d.createElement(s);js.id=id;js.src=p+\"://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\";fjs.parentNode.insertBefore(js,fjs);}}(document,\"script\",\"twitter-wjs\");</script>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '#ff9300', NULL, NULL, NULL),
