(5, 5, 'ENG', ' Development of Amravati MIDC top priority, says Pote', 'Amravati', 'Maharashtra', 'Amravati', '444602', 'From Member of Legislative Council (MLC) in 2012 to minister of state for industries, mining and environment in the Devendra Fadnavis government, it has been a meteoric rise in politics for Pravin Pote. The clean image of this leader from western Vidarbha is one of the factors behind his selection for the ministerial berth. Despite being part of the \'core circle\' of the CM, Pote says he is still a grassroots worker. \"I want to remain a party worker and not a minister who sits in a closed-door cabin,\" he says. Development of Amravati MIDC, Belora airport and railway wagon repairs factory in Badnera are his top priorities, besides making the city slum-free.', NULL, 0, 0, '2012-07-19 15:29:00', '2012-11-29 15:29:00', '1434978754-em.jpg', 'Image', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(6, 5, 'ENG', 'Fadnavis inaugurates textile park in Amravati', 'Amravati', 'Maharashtra', 'Amravati', '444602', 'Maharashtra CM Devendra fadnavis laid foundation stone for starting additional facilities for Textile Park in Nandgaon Peth MIDC, Amravati.\r\nHe also laid foundation stone for Siyaram Silk Mills. Siyaram is investing Rs 250 crore with an employment generation of 250. Industries Minister Shri Subhash Desai, Minister Shri Praveen Pote, Minister Ranjit Patil, MP Anand Adsul, MLA Sunil Deshmukh, Dr. Anil Bonde, MLA Yashomati Thakur too were present.', NULL, 0, 0, '2015-06-17 18:42:00', '2015-07-01 18:42:00', '1434978082-em.jpg', 'Image', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(7, 2, 'ENG', 'Congress puts off mega event on Ambedkar Jayanti', 'New Delhi', 'Delhi', 'Delhi', '110006', 'With Rahul Gandhi yet to return from his “sabbatical”, Congress has decided to hold a low-key function on Tuesday to mark the beginning of the year-long celebrations of B R Ambedkar’s 125th birth anniversary. While, senior leader Sushil Kumar Shinde would attend a function in Mhow, the birth place of Ambedkar, on Tuesday, the party would now kick-off the nationwide celebrations at an event in the Madhya Pradesh town next month, which will be attended by Rahul. Congress wanted to launch the celebrations in a big way, but Rahul’s unavailability forced it to redraw the schedule.', NULL, 0, 0, '2015-06-03 19:45:00', '2015-06-26 19:45:00', '1434981897-em.jpg', 'Image', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(8, 2, 'ENG', 'Freedom Movement', 'New Delhi', 'Delhi', 'Delhi', '110011', 'The Indian freedom movement was perhaps the greatest mass movement in world history. After 1919, it was built around the notion that people had to and could play an active role in politics and in their own liberation.', NULL, 0, 0, '2015-06-16 19:48:00', '2015-07-02 19:48:00', '1434982022-em.jpg', 'Image', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(9, 8, 'ENG', 'Union minister for home affairs Rajnath Singh on Friday asked the Punjab government ', 'Abdal', 'Punjab', 'Amritsar', '143502', 'Union minister for home affairs Rajnath Singh on Friday asked the Punjab government to make fight against drugs a people’s movement. He was addressing a congregation here to mark the 350th year of setting up of Anandpur Sahib by ninth Guru Tegh Bahadur.', NULL, 31.7426, 75.0794, '2015-06-16 13:42:00', '2015-07-02 13:42:00', '1435132920-em.jpg', 'Image', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, '2015-07-03 14:41:31'),
(10, 8, 'ENG', 'Home minister Rajnath Singh chose to speak much beyond his ministry\'s remit — on economy', 'Ayodhya ', 'Uttar Pradesh', 'Ayodhya ', '226021', 'Declaring himself to be a man for all seasons, home minister Rajnath Singh chose to speak much beyond his ministry\'s remit — on economy, diplomacy and the Ram temple — on Friday, signifying his official number 2 status in the Modi government.  Rajnath Singh today acknowledged that building of Ram temple in Ayodhya is an important issue and the Government would welcome an out of court settlement.', NULL, 26.7976, 82.2055, '2015-06-18 13:45:00', '2015-07-02 13:45:00', '1435133073-em.jpg', 'Image', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, '2015-07-03 14:41:08'),
(11, 8, 'ENG', 'Union Home Minister Rajnath Singh on Friday praised the Khalsa Panth, the Sikh community', 'Chheherta ', 'Punjab', 'Amritsar', '143105', 'Anandpur Sahib: Union Home Minister Rajnath Singh on Friday praised the Khalsa Panth, the Sikh community, for promoting secularism and the cultural heritage of the country. Addressing a gathering at the conclusion of the three-day celebrations of the 350th anniversary of the foundation of this historic Punjab town, he said the Sikhs and the Khalsa Panth played a great role not only in defending India but also promoting secularism and cultural heritage.', NULL, 31.6222, 74.7945, '2015-06-10 13:53:00', '2015-07-02 13:53:00', '1435133555-em.jpg', 'Image', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, '2015-07-03 14:41:26'),
(12, 8, 'ENG', 'Economic policies adopted by Narendra Modi government will be reflected on the ground', 'Raipur', 'Chhattisgarh', 'Raipur', '493332', 'RAIPUR:  The results of economic policies adopted by Narendra Modi government will be reflected on the ground in three years and the country will get \"complete economic freedom\" in five to seven years, Home Minister Rajnath Singh said today.\r\nAddressing a function after inaugurating the headquarters of the Chhattisgarh Police, Mr Singh said India had attained the political freedom years ago but the economic freedom is yet to be achieved.', NULL, 0, 0, '2015-06-09 13:55:00', '2015-07-02 13:55:00', '1555315326-em.png', 'Image', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, '2019-05-28 08:45:06'),
(13, 8, 'ENG', 'Rajnath visited Sukma and inaugurated the first fortified police station ', 'Sukma', 'Chhattisgarh', 'Sukma ', '494111', 'Home Minister Rajnath Singh on Sunday urged Maoists to drop their weapons and come back to the mainstream. - Rajnath visited Sukma and inaugurated the first fortified police station of the state in Dornapal. It is among 75 such stations being constructed in the state from the central funds. He also flew to the Chintagufa police camp, located near Tadmetla, where Maoists had killed 76 personnel in 2010.', NULL, 18.3911, 81.6593, '2015-06-02 14:00:00', '2015-06-25 14:00:00', '1435133971-em.jpg', 'Image', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, '2015-08-05 13:39:40'),
(14, 8, 'ENG', 'Rajnath Singh on Sunday stated that New Delhi has appealed to Pakistan to help in tackling terrorism', 'Near Airport', 'Delhi', 'New Delhi', '110001', 'Union Home Minister Rajnath Singh on Sunday stated that New Delhi has appealed to Pakistan to help in tackling terrorism.\r\n\r\n“We have appealed to Pakistan to help in tackling terrorism because Pakistan today is facing crisis due to terrorism. Our government is taking all possible measures to tackle terrorism. Not just India, but entire world knows who is responsible for terrorism,” Singh told the media here.', NULL, 28.6314, 77.2233, '2015-06-10 14:05:00', '2015-07-02 14:05:00', '1435134260-em.jpg', 'Image', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, '2015-08-05 13:39:05'),
