(32, 23, 'ENG', 'Navratri Festival signifies women power ', 'Raipur', 'Madhya Pradesh', 'Raipur', '492001', 'Chief Minister of Chhattisgarh Dr Raman Singh has greeted people on beginning of auspicious festival- Shardiya Navratri. In his message to public, Chief Minister has stated that this festival of worshipping nine avatars of Ma Durga on each of the nine days signifies women power in Indian culture. Dr Raman Singh said that Chhattisgarh also has the age-old tradition of \'Shakti Puja\'. Temples such as Bamleshwari Temple Dongargarh, Mahamaya Temple Ratanpur and Ambikapur, Danteshwari Temple Dantewada, Ganga Maiya Temple Jhalmala, Chandrahasini Temple Chandrapur, etc are the major centre of belief for devotees. Chief Minister has welcomed thousands of devotees visiting these centres of belief on the occasion of Shardiya Navratri and has extended best wishes for celebration of the festival. Dr Singh has instructed administrative officials of respective districts to arrange for all the necessary facilities for devotees visiting these temples. Dr Raman Singh said that on this auspicious festiva', NULL, 21.2514, 81.6296, '2015-10-12 10:00:00', '2015-10-12 12:00:00', '1450166096-em.jpg', 'Image', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, '2015-12-15 07:54:56'),
(33, 23, 'ENG', 'Mana Camp pond will be developed into \'Model\' one', 'Raipur', 'Madhya Pradesh', 'Raipur', '492001', 'Chief Minister Dr. Raman Singh today assured a delegation of visitors that the pond (Talab) located near Nagar Panchayat Mana Camp will be developed into a model one. The delegation was led by Nagar Panchayat President Mr. Shyama Prasad Chakraborthy. They met Chief Minister Dr. Raman Singh at the weekly \'Jan-Darshan\' programme at his official residence. He directed the memorandum   to Urban Administration and Development Minister Mr.  Amar Agrawal', NULL, 21.2514, 81.6296, '2015-10-08 16:00:00', '2015-10-08 18:00:00', '1450166342-em.jpg', 'Image', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, '2015-12-15 07:59:02'),
(34, 26, 'ENG', 'Jonbeel Mela ', 'Morigaon', 'Assam', 'Morigaon', '782410', 'Chief Minister Tarun Gogoi said that Jonbeel Mela is a great melting pot where people from all walks of life converge and forge a unifying force which has the potential to tame divisive forces.\r\n\r\nAddressing a gathering at Junbeel Mela at Morigaon on Saturday, Gogoi said that at Junbeel Mela people from all ethnicities converge and forge a greater understanding which has the potential to foil any evil design of divisive forces. Gogoi said, “Some divisive forces are hell bound to create division in the society in the name of caste, creed and religion to fulfil their narrow gains” adding that he said, “Such forces need to be controlled for the State to go forward and expedite its development”.', 'http://www.nelive.in/photo/north-east/news/photo-gallery-jan-23-2016', 26.1844, 92.229, '2016-01-23 18:15:00', '2016-03-30 18:15:00', '1453898472-em.png', 'Image', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, '2016-03-26 10:17:15'),
(36, 26, 'ENG', '12th South Asian Games, 2016', 'Sarusajai Stadium', 'Assam', 'Guwahati', '781028 ', 'The 12th South Asian Games started on 5th February 2016 in Guwahati and Shillong received a positive response with sports fanatics thronging the stadium to enjoy the twelve days of sporting activities in the spirit of friendship, togetherness and much more.\r\n\r\nWith 4500 participants, including 2600 athletes in 22 disciplines from 8 countries, the event has been widely hailed as the best South Asian Games, ever organised.\r\nA huge credit goes to Shri Tarun Gogoi, the honourable Chief Minister of Assam and Shri Mukul Sangma, the honourable Chief Minister of Meghalaya. The Government of India, the Government of Meghalaya and the Government of Assam worked in unison to bring the Games to the two cities', 'http://www.tarungogoi.in/pressrelease.php?displaytype=Press&displayid=PR-102846', 26.1218, 91.8001, '2016-02-05 18:20:00', '2016-02-16 18:20:00', '1453898596-em.png', 'Image', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, '2016-03-25 11:19:26'),
