(101, 30, 'ENG', NULL, 'दिंडोरी, नाशिक', 'Maharashtra', 'Nashik', '422202', NULL, NULL, 20.0417, 73.8052, '2015-01-03 11:38:00', '2015-01-03 12:30:00', '1462601273-em.jpg', 'Image', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, '2016-05-07 06:09:34'),
(102, 26, 'ENG', 'Assam CM attends Extended State Executive meeting of NSUI at Rajiv Bhawan ', 'Rajiv Bhawan, Guwahati', 'Assam', 'Guwahati', '781005', 'Assam Chief Minister attends Extended State Executive meeting of NSUI at Rajiv Bhawan today.\r\n\r\nAddressing the media, Shri Gogoi asserted, \"My Government has a great contribution to the nation during the freedom struggle. The BJP never participated in the struggle or in removing poverty  from our nation. So this is the basic difference between my party and BJP.\"\r\n\r\nTalking about equality, CM mentioned, \"The constitution gives equality to every individual. If we discriminate others on the basis of religion, we will hamper the unity and harmony of the state and the whole nation.\"', NULL, 26.1573, 91.7953, '2016-05-08 12:30:00', '2016-05-08 14:00:00', '1462727362-em.jpg', 'Image', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, '2016-05-08 17:09:23'),
(103, 26, 'ENG', 'Shri Gogoi\'s Autobiography Released', 'Guwahati', 'Assam', 'Guwahati', '781005', 'Hon\'ble Chief Minister, Shri Tarun Gogoi released his autobiography \'Turnaround: Leading Assam From The Front\'\r\n\r\nIn the autobiography, Shri Gogoi has mentioned his entire journey of his life. From his close association with the Gandhi family to the toughest period of his life.', NULL, 26.1573, 91.7953, '2016-05-15 22:55:00', '2016-05-15 22:55:00', '1463333295-em.png', 'Image', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, '2016-05-15 17:28:15'),
(104, 26, 'ENG', 'Shri Gogoi accepts his defeat and congratulates Shri Sarbananda Sonowal ', 'Dispur', 'Assam', 'Guwahati', '781005', 'Shri Tarun Gogoi accepts his defeat but not disheartened as he believes his supporters are always with him as he wins fromTitabor constituency defeating BJP\'s Kamakhya Prasad Tasa.\r\n\r\nShri Tarun Gogoi further adds keeping himself calm and composed as always, \" We are sad but not out of hope. Losing  and winning is a part of Democracy. I congratulate Sarbananda Sonowal for this grand success.\"', NULL, 26.1433, 91.7898, '2016-05-19 15:11:00', '2016-05-19 15:11:00', '1463651096-em.png', 'Image', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, '2016-05-19 09:47:17'),
(105, 26, 'ENG', 'Shri Tarun Gogoi tendered his resignation as CM', 'Raj Bhawan ', 'Assam', 'Guwahati', '781005', 'Shri Tarun Gogoi submits  his resignation as CM at Raj Bhavan yesterday following his party\'s defeat  at the  Assembly election, however, Governor PB Acharya has asked him to continue as CM till the new CM comes into power.\r\n\r\nMr. Gogoi who had been in power for more than a decade held his last cabinet meeting with his ministerial colleagues and offered his gratitude to all officers and government employees for being with him since 2001.\r\n\r\nShri Gogoi also vacated the CM residence yesterday he was residing in since the time he got into power. ', NULL, 26.1573, 91.7953, '2016-05-20 12:48:00', '2016-05-20 12:48:00', '1463815374-em.JPG', 'Image', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, '2016-05-21 07:22:54'),
(106, 32, 'ENG', 'Convocation Ceremony ', 'Kolhapur, Maharashtra', 'Maharashtra', 'Kolhapur', '416001', 'Shri Bhaiyyuji Maharaj was conferred upon with D. Litt. degree at fourth convocation ceremony of D. Y. Patil University, Kolhapur on April 13 this month by the Chief guest of the function Dr. K. N. Ganesh (Director, IISER, Pune).', NULL, 16.705, 74.2433, '2016-04-13 14:25:00', '2016-04-13 14:25:00', '1465462360-em.jpg', 'Image', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, '2016-06-09 09:05:34'),
