(60, 'Nitul Kalita', '9707010490', 'Sir, Agriculture is the main back bond Indian economics. Increasing production and productivity will boost our economic condition as well as increase our GDP and ultimate development of our state. Lots of central sector and state schemes are on going in our state but development is very less, because delay of fund release from state treasury( ceiling delay). \nMoreover in agriculture department one CSS- agriculture technology management agency(ATMA)  is running. Under this lots of talented young professionals ( PhD, PG, GRADUATE , Agriculture, veterinary fishery) are working as a contractual employee. For development of farmers,they are doing hard work. but lots of talented person are leaving their job due to job insecurity, I.e. ultimate loss is farmers. It is my humble request if you make permanent their jobs. then they will give more service as they are young professionals and ultimate development of the state.', 26, 383, '2016-03-29 05:08:53'),
(61, 'Jyotiprasad kalita', '7896792185', 'first of all sir I have really honoured you as a veteran leader and CM of Assam . As I personally feel in Assam mainly unemployment is a burning problem for MBA, Masscom and other graduates . After passing out in Assam its been a difficult task to get an incredible job due to the lack of corporates mainly  mncs , start ups are needed in Assam which will resolve various problems of Unemployment . Because of lack of mncs and big companies as an MBA I have facing  critical problem in start my career in Assam because for freshers jobs are not there in Assam . Therefore sir emphasis on solving infrastructural problems , reducing the gap of skill where right talent shape with right opportunities . finally its worth mentioning congress has done various work in various sector but still lots to go and needs to do more work in the ground level so that unemployment problem would be deter out .', 26, 398, '2016-03-29 06:17:01'),
